pr-for-commit <commit-ish>

Print the GitHub PR URL that introduced a given commit into the
default branch of the current repo.

Resolution strategy (first match wins):

  1. Ask the GitHub API directly via
     `gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/commits/<sha>/pulls`. This handles
     squash-merged PRs (where the commit on main IS the PR head
     commit).
  2. Walk merge commits between <sha> and origin/<default-branch>
     in oldest-first order and parse the PR number out of the merge
     commit subject. This handles classic
     "Merge pull request #N from ..." merges where the original
     commit SHA is preserved on main.

Examples:

  pr-for-commit 09fca5a
  pr-for-commit HEAD~5

Requires: gh, git.
